			<h3>Futpong Challenge</h3>
			<p>Taking the Futpong Challenge is easy.</p>
			<ol>
				<li>Assess skill level. Give players five minutes to get the highest number of juggles in a row with an age appropriate soccer ball.</li>
				<li>Show them how to play Futpong and send them home with a set.  Give them one month to play as many games as possible (minimum 30, but better to play 50-60 games).</li>
				<li>Bring them back together for a Futpong Tournament.</li>
				<li>After the tournament give them another five minute skill assessment.</li>
				
			</ol>
			<p>Encourage the kids to juggle as much as possible during the month with their Futpong ball - it'll make their Futpong play better and you'll be amazed at the skill development.</p>
