			<h3>Futpong Tournament</h3>
			<p>We've developed official tournament rules - download them below.  We've hosted tournaments in a variety of ways, but the following approach seems to work best:</p>
			
			<ol>
				<li>Setup enough courts for all players to participate</li>
				<li>Tell the players that one end of the line of courts is for the most skilled players and one end is for the least skilled players</li>
				<li>Allow the players to chose which court to start playing on</li>
				<li>Play games for five minutes after which the winner advances one court to the more skilled side and the loser moves one court to the less skilled side</li>
				<li>Play enough games so that any player would have had an opportunity to move to the most skilled court if they had one all of their games</li>
				<li>Have the players on the top two courts play semi final and final elimination rounds.</li>
				<li>Award a trophy to your Futpong Master!</li>
				
			</ol>
			
			<p>Best to split the courts into two columns if you have more than 8 courts in your tournament.</p>
			
